title: For Sale:  U.S. Model 1816 A. Waters Musket (.69 Cal)
postcontent:
For sale is a U.S. Model 1816 A. Waters  Musket. A. Waters was one of several contract makers for the M1816. This musket was manufactured in 1832 and has all the cartouche marks and proper stampings on the metal. It was converted to caplock. It is conceivable that this musket saw action in the Mexican-American War, Indian Wars, and early part of the Civil War. Shoots good for a musket. 

This is an example of a Third Type Model 1816 musket from a contract for 21,560 muskets manufactured by Asa Waters of Millbury, Massachusetts between 1817 and 1836. It has the Waters Third Type marking of "US / A. WATERS" in front of the hammer and "MILLBURY / 1832" vertically behind the hammer. The barrel at the breech is marked "P" and "M". The left side plate is marked "V" and "J", and the front of the trigger guard plate is marked "C" and "J". Three iron barrel bands, iron button head ramrod, and sling swivels. The buttplate tang is marked "US".
